  - Wistia's favorite vim setup


To install whim:

  1) Clone whim into ~/.whim:

    $ cd ~/
    $ git clone git://github.com/wistia/whim.git .whim

  2) Edit your .vimrc to include this line:

    source ~/.whim/init.vim
    
  3) Edit your .gvimrc to include this line:
  
    source ~/.whim/ginit.vim

  4) This step is optional. If you want your command-t plugin to work:

    $ cd ~/.whim/ruby/command-t
    $ make

  5) Restart (mac)vim!
